  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accounts Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Manage the full spectrum of accounting functions, ensuring accuracy and compliance with company policies</p></li><li><p>Record and process all invoices in the accounting system in a timely and precise manner</p></li><li><p>Prepare, review, and reconcile intercompany transactions and balances</p></li><li><p>Conduct regular bank reconciliations and ensure alignment with financial records</p></li><li><p>Assist in the preparation and submission of GST returns, ensuring regulatory compliance</p></li><li><p>Liaise with auditors, tax agents, and other professional advisors during audits and compliance reviews</p></li><li><p>Provide administrative and operational support to the accounting department, including filing, data management, and record maintenance</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field</p></li><li><p>Minimum of 3 years’ experience in accounting within a local construction firm, with exposure to audits</p></li><li><p>Highly meticulous with strong organizational, analytical, and communication skills</p></li><li><p>Able to perform effectively under pressure, meet tight deadlines, and maintain a positive attitude</p></li><li><p>Self-motivated, quick learner, and a collaborative team player</p></li></ul>",
